    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1881-03-07T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1881-03-07T00:00:00-05:00" n="277" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d277">
                <head>No. 273.<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Evarts</persName> to Mr. <persName type="to">Outrey</persName>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1881-03-07">
                            <hi rend="italic">March</hi> 7,
                                1881</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have had the honor to receive your note
                            of this day’s date, in which you inform me that the minister of foreign
                            affairs of France has renewed to you the declarations made by his
                            predecessors, and has authorized you to affirm once more the
                            unchangeable resolution of the French Government to maintain the
                            absolutely private and international character of the enterprise of
                            Monsieur de Lesseps.</p>
                <p>Thanking you for these renewed assurances, I have the honor, &amp;c.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>WM. M. EVARTS.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
